    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Figures and ornaments made in plaster of Paris to imitate Staffordshire pottery and other works. The works were not fired but painted or left in their natural white color. The works were popular in the United States in the 18th and 19th centuries.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
